**Overall Meaning:**

This verse emphasizes the unity and pure nature of consciousness, stating that all diverse powers (vichitra shaktaya) within the universe are essentially pure (svacha) and operate in unison (sama). These powers are not separate or fragmented, but arise from the unchangeable, unified consciousness (nirvikaraya cita). 

This consciousness acts freely (kriyante) without any limitations of parts (kala) or functions (kalana). This verse emphasizes the interconnectedness of all existence and highlights the pure, undifferentiated nature of consciousness, the source of all activity and power. 
